to make certain vows,

16:17.240 --> 16:22.000
now, not just to each other
but to the Lord Almighty himself.
Now, do you understand this?

16:22.000 --> 16:24.160
Yes. What vows?

16:24.160 --> 16:28.000
Well, to bring your children up
as strong and Christian soldiers.

16:28.000 --> 16:31.320
Are we expecting a war, Father?
LAUGHTER

16:31.320 --> 16:35.680
And you know the church's stance
on contraception and divorce?

16:35.680 --> 16:37.840
Yes, and you need to cop on.

16:39.360 --> 16:43.440
Look, Father, if you don't play the
game, don't make the feckin' rules!

16:44.960 --> 16:47.200
Mrs Brown!

16:47.200 --> 16:50.680
Father, marriages aren't made in
heaven, they're made here in Finglas,

16:50.680 --> 16:52.880
or in Birmingham,
or Liverpool, or New York.

16:52.880 --> 16:54.480
And it's tough.

16:56.240 --> 16:58.480
You fight with each other,
you love each other

16:58.480 --> 17:02.000
and sometimes you'll feckin' hate
each other. But with God's help...

17:02.000 --> 17:03.360
Ah, "With God's help..."

17:03.360 --> 17:06.040
God'll help you stay sane,
the rest is up to you!

17:06.040 --> 17:08.840
It's about respect
and learning to love!

17:08.840 --> 17:12.280
Yes, and children! Learning to
love your children, no matter what.

17:12.280 --> 17:15.560
Whether they go to prison, or lock
themselves in a feckin' cupboard,

17:15.560 --> 17:18.480
or even if they're homosexual.
Am I right, Father?

17:18.480 --> 17:21.800
Well, er...homosexual is a bit...
LAUGHTER

17:21.800 --> 17:24.840
And if you get it right, and I
think these two have got it right...

17:24.840 --> 17:26.800
Oh, Maria,

17:26.800 --> 17:29.840
you can be happy. Happier
than you ever thought possible.

17:31.080 --> 17:33.400
There's your
pre-marriage chat, Maria...

17:33.400 --> 17:35.880
Do you have anything
to add to that, Father?

17:37.600 --> 17:38.720
No.

17:40.160 --> 17:41.720
Not a thing. Thank you, Father.

17:41.720 --> 17:43.880
Goodnight and God bless you.

17:48.360 --> 17:53.040
KNOCKING
Goodnight, Dermot. Father, you're
talking to the ironing board now.

17:53.040 --> 17:54.800
LAUGHTER

17:54.800 --> 17:57.400
KNOCKING
Goodnight, Dermot.

17:57.400 --> 17:58.440
Goodnight, Father.

18:06.160 --> 18:08.160
Rory...

18:08.160 --> 18:10.720
I want to talk to you...
about your illness.

18:10.720 --> 18:12.200
LAUGHTER

18:12.200 --> 18:15.080
Mammy, it's not an illness!
Well, it's not normal!

18:15.080 --> 18:16.560
Mammy!

18:17.760 --> 18:18.960
Fine.

18:18.960 --> 18:20.320
Rory...

18:20.320 --> 18:22.640
what I'm trying to say is...

18:22.640 --> 18:27.400
you are what you are. Whatever you
are, I will always be your mother.

18:27.400 --> 18:30.760
And I want you to know that it
doesn't matter how far we are apart,

18:30.760 --> 18:34.360
or long we are apart,
I will always be here waiting...

18:34.360 --> 18:35.680
with a loving heart.

18:35.680 --> 18:38.080
Awww! It's nice, isn't it? Yeah.

18:38.080 --> 18:39.760
I read it on a card!

18:39.760 --> 18:42.400
LAUGHTER

18:42.400 --> 18:44.040
May you rest in peace.

18:44.040 --> 18:46.880
LAUGHTER

18:46.880 --> 18:48.240
Mammy!

18:48.240 --> 18:49.840
Sorry.

18:51.160 --> 18:53.960
Rory,
what I am trying to say is...

18:53.960 --> 18:58.080
have you ever considered
that you might be...homosexual?

18:59.840 --> 19:03.520
Now, I know this comes
as a bit of a shock.

19:03.520 --> 19:08.720
And you probably want to think about
it, but here's a book. Here!

19:08.720 --> 19:10.480
That'll explain everything,

19:10.480 --> 19:14.280
except why Cathy hasn't got
a boyfriend even though
she's not lesbian or gay.

19:14.280 --> 19:16.160
Mammy!

19:16.160 --> 19:18.280
Sorry.

19:18.280 --> 19:20.280
Thanks, Mammy.

19:26.800 --> 19:28.560
Oh, you're hurting Mammy now!

19:29.760 --> 19:32.240
OK, erm...

19:32.240 --> 19:34.840
I'd better go and...read.
Do, love.

19:38.640 --> 19:41.120
Well, Mammy, I thought
you handled that very well.

19:41.120 --> 19:43.480
It wasn't easy, it was difficult.

19:43.480 --> 19:47.080
I hope Rory never has to have that
talk with any of his own children.

19:47.080 --> 19:49.760
LAUGHTER

19:53.520 --> 19:55.960
Dermot, love...

19:55.960 --> 19:58.800
your wedding suit is here.
I don't care!

20:01.560 --> 20:04.320
You should go up and have a bath
for the big day tomorrow.

20:04.320 --> 20:06.160
No. Go away.

20:09.160 --> 20:11.280
Cathy, what are we going to do?

20:11.280 --> 20:15.760
The wedding's tomorrow and we won't
all fit in that fuckin' cupboard!

20:17.520 --> 20:19.920
Mrs Brown,
I think I have it this time...

20:19.920 --> 20:23.720
Lovely. Leave it on the table,
Buster. I'll read it later.

20:23.720 --> 20:25.520
God, Buster, you look exhausted!

20:25.520 --> 20:28.120
I am, Cathy,
I haven't slept for two days.

20:28.120 --> 20:31.040
Well, you want to sleep tonight.
We need you fresh tomorrow!

20:31.040 --> 20:33.040
Don't worry.

20:33.040 --> 20:37.120
Hold on, Buster. Yeah? Read this
to Mammy and see what she thinks.

20:37.120 --> 20:40.720
Leave it there. I'll read it later.
No, Mammy. Listen now. Sit down.

20:40.720 --> 20:41.880
Here, Buster...

20:41.880 --> 20:43.480
Read!

20:48.720 --> 20:49.800
HE CLEARS HIS THROAT

20:49.800 --> 20:52.640
"Ladies and gentlemen
and the Reverend Father."

20:52.640 --> 20:54.840
Yeah, very well done, well done.

20:56.280 --> 20:58.880
"Can you believe that
Dermot Brown is married?

20:58.880 --> 21:00.480
"And to such a beautiful girl."

21:02.080 --> 21:03.640
From there.

21:05.400 --> 21:08.520
But you're skipping me joke about
the camel, the nun and the coconut!

21:08.520 --> 21:12.000
We'll live... read!

21:12.000 --> 21:14.880
Let's hope the camel does.

21:14.880 --> 21:19.800
"I don't know why Dermo picked me
to be his best friend...

21:19.800 --> 21:22.120
"but I'm really glad he did.

21:22.120 --> 21:26.000
"All I ever wanted to be
when I grew up was Dermot Brown.

21:29.320 --> 21:32.240
"He's the one who makes you laugh

21:32.240 --> 21:33.920
"even when you're in prison."

21:35.800 --> 21:37.480
I'll take that out.

21:40.760 --> 21:47.120
"I don't know why, but someone,
somewhere looked down on me
and thought...

21:47.120 --> 21:50.280
"'that eejit
needs a guardian angel'...

21:54.040 --> 21:56.800
"..and they sent Dermot Brown."

21:59.200 --> 22:01.080
I'm going up for me bath!

22:04.000 --> 22:06.760
So, what do you want changed?

22:08.280 --> 22:11.560
Nothing. I think it's
absolutely perfect, Buster.

22:11.560 --> 22:13.680
Oh, yes!

22:16.200 --> 22:20.280
HE SNORES

22:20.280 --> 22:22.560
LAUGHTER

22:26.720 --> 22:30.120
So, Winnie, Jacko's blind now, is he?

22:30.120 --> 22:31.720
It was his own fault, Agnes.

22:31.720 --> 22:34.920
He was dying for a cigarette as
soon as he got out of that hospital!

22:34.920 --> 22:37.400
If only he'd taken off
the oxygen mask!

22:38.680 --> 22:40.200
Yeah.

22:40.200 --> 22:42.040
LAUGHTER

22:43.040 --> 22:45.200
Whooooo! Wah-hey!

22:45.200 --> 22:48.600
God, I'd nearly go straight myself!

22:48.600 --> 22:51.480
Really?! No!

22:51.480 --> 22:54.200
Not even Father Quinn
will be safe today!

22:54.200 --> 22:55.240
Shag off!

22:59.160 --> 23:01.120
Well, well, Cathy.

23:01.120 --> 23:03.120
You look different!

23:03.120 --> 23:07.760
So what do you think, Mammy? I think
you've never looked more beautiful.

23:09.560 --> 23:12.000
Mammy, that's the suit
from Marcelle's window.

23:12.000 --> 23:15.440
Isn't it beautiful? You couldn't
afford that. Where did you get it?

23:15.440 --> 23:19.400
It was a surprise, I came out
of the shower and someone left it
on the bed for me!

23:22.360 --> 23:24.480
LAUGHTER

23:26.080 --> 23:28.440
LAUGHTER

23:29.600 --> 23:31.480
Grandad, you can't go like that!

23:31.480 --> 23:33.920
Ma, Grandad's stripped again!

23:33.920 --> 23:37.800
Oh, for God's sake, Cathy.
I thought I told you to dress him!

23:37.800 --> 23:40.560
Yeah, Mammy, twice already.
He keeps taking off the suit!

23:40.560 --> 23:42.600
Well, go back up and put it on him.

23:42.600 --> 23:45.520
And staple the feckin' thing
to him if you have to!

23:47.600 --> 23:50.480
Well, at least he's wearing
more than Cathy!

23:50.480 --> 23:54.040
Careful, Winnie, you'll end up having
a meal through a tube beside Jacko.

23:55.800 --> 23:59.520
"Ladies and gentlemen
and the Reverend Father..."

23:59.520 --> 24:01.480
Yeah! We've heard it before. Get out!

24:03.000 --> 24:04.280
Here, Agnes...

24:04.280 --> 24:06.760
remember the excitement
the morning of my wedding?

24:06.760 --> 24:09.000
I do. Sure, mine was the same!

24:09.000 --> 24:12.920
I remember standing on the altar and
the priest looked at me and he said,

24:12.920 --> 24:14.680
"Agnes, do you take...

24:14.680 --> 24:18.960
"this...to be
your lawfully wedded husband?"

24:18.960 --> 24:24.720
And I remember, I looked
into Jacko's eyes and I whispered,
"I do".

24:24.720 --> 24:28.680
I remember, I looked into
Redser's eyes and I said,

24:28.680 --> 24:30.040
"I'll see."

24:32.320 --> 24:34.720
Here, you had that Father...

24:34.720 --> 24:36.640
Oh, what was his name? Oh, erm...

24:36.640 --> 24:39.600
Father McCrum!
Right, Agnes, McCrum.

24:39.600 --> 24:41.680
And in his deep voice, he said,

24:41.680 --> 24:44.960
"I now pronounce you man and wife!"
Yes...

24:44.960 --> 24:46.680
and then me waters broke! Yeah!

24:46.680 --> 24:49.560
LAUGHTER

24:49.560 --> 24:52.000
Well, someone's having a good time!

24:52.000 --> 24:54.920
Hello! Hiya!
We were just over at Maria's...

24:54.920 --> 24:58.760
She looks stunning! Does she?
And her hair's only fabulous!

24:58.760 --> 24:59.960
Of course!

24:59.960 --> 25:02.160
OK, everybody.

25:02.160 --> 25:04.040
It's the big moment.

25:04.040 --> 25:07.440
Ladies and gentlemen...
Dermot Brown!

25:07.440 --> 25:10.720
THEY CHEER

25:13.280 --> 25:15.120
Oh, my God, Dermot...

25:15.120 --> 25:17.920
you look amazing! Thanks, Mammy!

25:17.920 --> 25:20.880
It only feels like yesterday
I was bathing you...

25:20.880 --> 25:22.320
It was yesterday!

25:22.320 --> 25:25.000
LAUGHTER

25:25.000 --> 25:26.480
Dermot, son...

25:26.480 --> 25:29.600
I've never told you
that I'm proud of you.

25:31.680 --> 25:34.320
Right.
LAUGHTER

25:34.320 --> 25:38.640
Let's get down to the church
and get this thing feckin' started!

25:38.640 --> 25:41.840
Get the flowers! Get the flowers!

25:41.840 --> 25:43.520
I'll get the feckin' flowers!

25:48.440 --> 25:50.760
Well, that's that then...

25:50.760 --> 25:53.080
Another one gone. Huh!

25:55.680 --> 25:59.560
It's always difficult for a mother
when another one leaves the nest.

25:59.560 --> 26:01.320
But that's our job, you know,

26:01.320 --> 26:05.200
to get them ready to go out into
the mad, mad world on their own.

26:07.800 --> 26:12.240
It'll be strange to look
into Dermot's bedroom
and just see an empty bed...

26:12.240 --> 26:15.240
and a stack of dirty magazines!
LAUGHTER

26:15.240 --> 26:16.840
Mammy! Dermot?

26:16.840 --> 26:20.440
Is there any chance Maria and me
can stay here for a while,

26:20.440 --> 26:22.160
just until we get
a place of our own?

26:22.160 --> 26:26.400
Of course. You and Maria can stay
here for as long as you like.
As long as you feckin' like!

26:26.400 --> 26:30.200
Thanks, Ma.
That's a load off me mind.

26:30.200 --> 26:31.720
It's a load off my mind!

26:31.720 --> 26:34.040
DOOR SHUTS

26:35.440 --> 26:37.480
Will I ever get feckin' rid of them?

26:38.880 --> 26:40.200
I'll see you, goodbye!

26:41.840 --> 26:43.040
APPLAUSE

